{"_id":"2jGP3xJgARI3AEbI","name":"Crippling Blow","permission":{"default":0,"lNumE4kwYfzQkIkY":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"type":"String","label":"Description","value":"<p>You can focus your entire body into a single, brutal close combat attack. For your Action, you may attempt a <strong>Challenging (+0) Strength</strong> Test. If you succeed, and you successfully attack an opponent before the end of the next Round, you inflict a Critical Wound, ignoring Critical Deflections. You can use Crippling Blow a number of times per encounter equal to your Crippling Blow level. For every +2 SL on the Strength Test, you increase the result on the Critical Wounds Table by +10.</p>"},"gmdescription":{"type":"String","label":"Description","value":""},"max":{"type":"String","label":"Max Advances","value":"s"},"advances":{"type":"Number","label":"Advances","value":1},"career":{"value":"","type":"String","label":"Career"},"tests":{"type":"String","label":"Tests","value":"Strength for Crippling Blow"}},"flags":{},"img":"modules/nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e/icons/talents/crippling-blow.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"ClCysnqhJTh8FE8Q","name":"Blind Fighter","permission":{"default":0,"lNumE4kwYfzQkIkY":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"type":"String","label":"Description","value":"<p>Years of practice and development of other senses allows you to fight in close combat without the benefit of sight. This Talent reduces the penalties for fighting with a melee weapon while suffering from obscured vision, permitting you to fight in fog, smoke, or darkness more effectively. You can ignore the -10 penalty from a @Condition[Blinded] Condition. Each level in this Talent lets you ignore the -10 penalty from an extra @Condition[Blinded] Condition. Note this Talent only improves a character&rsquo;s chances to hit with melee weapons and has no effect on ranged weapon attacks.</p>"},"gmdescription":{"type":"String","label":"Description","value":""},"max":{"type":"String","label":"Max Advances","value":"i"},"advances":{"type":"Number","label":"Advances","value":1},"career":{"value":"","type":"String","label":"Career"},"tests":{"type":"String","label":"Tests","value":""}},"flags":{},"img":"modules/nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e/icons/talents/blind-fighter.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"QjBPhJr6L3c2TMIn","name":"Armor-Monger","permission":{"default":0,"lNumE4kwYfzQkIkY":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"type":"String","label":"Description","value":"<p>You are a skilled armorer, constantly tinkering and improving your armor, or keeping it in pristine shape by repairing the slightest damage it sustains. You even learned to enhance the protection afforded by your armor and how to use it optimally. Increase the Armor Points of any armor you wear by 1 on all locations it would normally cover, so long as you spend at least an hour each day to clean and repair it or make minor modifications. This bonus applies only to armor when worn by you, cannot be used for Critical Deflection<em> (WHFRP 4E Core Book, page 299)</em> and does not count towards the armor&rsquo;s durability. If your armor&rsquo;s durability is reduced to 0 and made useless, the AP bonus no longer applies until it is repaired.</p>"},"gmdescription":{"type":"String","label":"Description","value":""},"max":{"type":"String","label":"Max Advances","value":"dex"},"advances":{"type":"Number","label":"Advances","value":1},"career":{"value":"","type":"String","label":"Career"},"tests":{"type":"String","label":"Tests","value":"Trade Tests for crafting and repairing armor"}},"flags":{},"img":"modules/nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e/icons/talents/armor-monger.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"RQ8KI3q2n61ZssBJ","name":"Creative Fighter","permission":{"default":0,"lNumE4kwYfzQkIkY":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"type":"String","label":"Description","value":"<p>You see everything as a potential weapon and can easily kill wielding anything you can get your hands on. From chairs, to candelabrums and makeshift tools, you&rsquo;re as deadly without a sword as you would be with one. Improvised weapons gain +1 Damage for every level of Creative Fighter. If you have this Talent thrice, you count all improvised weapons as having the <em>Undamaging </em>Flaw removed.</p>"},"gmdescription":{"type":"String","label":"Description","value":""},"max":{"type":"String","label":"Max Advances","value":"none"},"advances":{"type":"Number","label":"Advances","value":1},"career":{"value":"","type":"String","label":"Career"},"tests":{"type":"String","label":"Tests","value":""}},"flags":{},"img":"modules/nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e/icons/talents/creative-fighter.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"VANOdNWFo3P9gzxg","name":"Ambusher","permission":{"default":0,"lNumE4kwYfzQkIkY":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"type":"String","label":"Description","value":"<p>A battle is easily won if the enemy does not know they are fighting. You take this tactic to heart, striving to always seize the initiative and make the most of the element of surprise to finish fights before they truly begin. Your melee attacks against @Condition[Surprised] Targets gain a SL bonus equal to your levels of Ambusher.</p>"},"gmdescription":{"type":"String","label":"Description","value":""},"max":{"type":"String","label":"Max Advances","value":"ag"},"advances":{"type":"Number","label":"Advances","value":1},"career":{"value":"","type":"String","label":"Career"},"tests":{"type":"String","label":"Tests","value":"Melee when attacking a Surprised target"}},"flags":{},"img":"modules/nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e/icons/talents/ambusher.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"YsiPBxZ3kD9rviNA","name":"Bombardier","permission":{"default":0,"lNumE4kwYfzQkIkY":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"type":"String","label":"Description","value":"<p>Due to many years of training, and an obsession that others might find unnerving, you are an expert with explosive weapons and have an uncanny control over where projectiles land. You double the Range you can throw explosives, and if any thrown explosive Scatters you roll twice to determine the direction and distance of the explosive and may choose either result.</p>"},"gmdescription":{"type":"String","label":"Description","value":""},"max":{"type":"String","label":"Max Advances","value":"bs"},"advances":{"type":"Number","label":"Advances","value":1},"career":{"value":"","type":"String","label":"Career"},"tests":{"type":"String","label":"Tests","value":"Extended Trade (Explosives) Tests"}},"flags":{},"img":"modules/nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e/icons/talents/bombardier.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"aJA3QqdN2xXQFaV1","name":"Hammer Swing","permission":{"default":0,"lNumE4kwYfzQkIkY":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"type":"String","label":"Description","value":"<p>You strike blows with such focus and force that it breaks armor and pulps flesh as it strikes. When using a single-handed melee weapon with two hands to make a single melee attack, you add +1 Strength Bonus to the attack. Any Melee (Two-handed) weapon with the <em>Hack </em>or <em>Pummel </em>Quality may also count as having the <em>Impact </em>Quality for a number of attacks equal to your level of Hammer Swing per day, to represent the shocking force of your blow&rsquo;s impacts. Any attack made using the <em>Impact </em>Quality in this manner after expending your daily uses requires a <strong>Very Hard (-30) Endurance</strong> Test. If failed, you receive one @Condition[Fatigued] Condition.</p>"},"gmdescription":{"type":"String","label":"Description","value":""},"max":{"type":"String","label":"Max Advances","value":"s"},"advances":{"type":"Number","label":"Advances","value":1},"career":{"value":"","type":"String","label":"Career"},"tests":{"type":"String","label":"Tests","value":""}},"flags":{},"img":"modules/nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e/icons/talents/hammerswing.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"cB6CCW3aU02tH2MW","name":"Tireless","permission":{"default":0,"lNumE4kwYfzQkIkY":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"type":"String","label":"Description","value":"<p>Through brute force of will or extreme physical resilience, you can carry on through extreme adversity and exhaustion without losing significant efficiency. You can ignore the -10 penalty from a @Condition[Fatigued] Condition. Each level in this Talent lets you ignore the -10 penalty from an extra @Condition[Fatigued] Condition.</p>"},"gmdescription":{"type":"String","label":"Description","value":""},"max":{"type":"String","label":"Max Advances","value":"t"},"advances":{"type":"Number","label":"Advances","value":1},"career":{"value":"","type":"String","label":"Career"},"tests":{"type":"String","label":"Tests","value":""}},"flags":{},"img":"modules/nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e/icons/talents/tireless.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"dzuzDXPEgZs5w1El","name":"Volley Shot","permission":{"default":0,"lNumE4kwYfzQkIkY":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"type":"String","label":"Description","value":"<p>You have trained extensively with your fellow marksman, ensuring that your shots are perfectly timed to inflict maximum damage upon the enemy. If an enemy causes you to lose Advantage when standing beside an active ally with the Volley Shot Talent, you may keep 1 lost Advantage for each time you&rsquo;ve taken the Volley Shot Talent.</p>"},"gmdescription":{"type":"String","label":"Description","value":""},"max":{"type":"String","label":"Max Advances","value":"bs"},"advances":{"type":"Number","label":"Advances","value":1},"career":{"value":"","type":"String","label":"Career"},"tests":{"type":"String","label":"Tests","value":"Ranged Tests when beside an ally with Volley Shot"}},"flags":{},"img":"modules/nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e/icons/talents/volley-shot.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"ijvxbPdaMBblJ3b2","name":"Overkill","permission":{"default":0,"lNumE4kwYfzQkIkY":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"type":"String","label":"Description","value":"<p>You have spent enough time fighting the enemies of the Old World to know that some creatures do not die when all sense says that they should expire, and that it is better to be safe than sorry when dealing with the unknown. Once per encounter, when you hit with a ranged attack, you may make a <strong>Challenging (+0) Perception </strong>Test. If successful, you add the SL to the Ranged Test for the attack. If you have the @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.talents.9h82z72XGo9tfgQS]{Acute Sense (Sight)} Talent, any benefits you receive from it may be applied to this Talent.</p>"},"gmdescription":{"type":"String","label":"Description","value":""},"max":{"type":"String","label":"Max Advances","value":"1"},"advances":{"type":"Number","label":"Advances","value":1},"career":{"value":"","type":"String","label":"Career"},"tests":{"type":"String","label":"Tests","value":""}},"flags":{},"img":"modules/nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e/icons/talents/overkill.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"lheO9kUQD7NKjOj2","name":"Guardian","permission":{"default":0,"lNumE4kwYfzQkIkY":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"type":"String","label":"Description","value":"<p>You have developed a sense of loyalty and comradery to your friends and allies and are even willing to trade your own life to protect others. As an Action at the start of the Round instead of on your Turn you may switch places with an ally within 2 yards, so long as there is no physical obstruction to prevent it. The ally no longer counts as Engaged during the switch. The character becomes the target of any attacks previously targeting the ally.</p>"},"gmdescription":{"type":"String","label":"Description","value":""},"max":{"type":"String","label":"Max Advances","value":"1"},"advances":{"type":"Number","label":"Advances","value":1},"career":{"value":"","type":"String","label":"Career"},"tests":{"type":"String","label":"Tests","value":""}},"flags":{},"img":"modules/nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e/icons/talents/guardian.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"o7uGMfttFKzu6AyW","name":"True Grit","permission":{"default":0,"lNumE4kwYfzQkIkY":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"type":"String","label":"Description","value":"<p>You can shrug off wounds that would fell lesser beings. Whenever you suffer Critical Wounds, you may make a <strong>Challenging (+0) @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.CcNJsS4jSwB6Ug1J]{Endurance} </strong>Test. If successful, you may reduce the result of the Critical Wound by 10 per level of True Grit. This Endurance Test is often modified by the Strength behind the blow that hit you: for every +10 Strength the blow has over your Toughness, you suffer a penalty of -10 to the @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.CcNJsS4jSwB6Ug1J]{Endurance} Test, and vice versa.</p>"},"gmdescription":{"type":"String","label":"Description","value":""},"max":{"type":"String","label":"Max Advances","value":"t"},"advances":{"type":"Number","label":"Advances","value":1},"career":{"value":"","type":"String","label":"Career"},"tests":{"type":"String","label":"Tests","value":""}},"flags":{},"img":"modules/nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e/icons/talents/true-grit.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"sHk3OncCfHj6hU4L","name":"Quick Draw","permission":{"default":0,"lNumE4kwYfzQkIkY":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"type":"String","label":"Description","value":"<p>You have practiced so frequently with your weapons that they practically leap into your hands in response to a simple thought. Once per Round, you can draw and ready a one-handed weapon for free without the use of a Free Action outside of the normal Initiative sequence.</p>"},"gmdescription":{"type":"String","label":"Description","value":""},"max":{"type":"String","label":"Max Advances","value":"dex"},"advances":{"type":"Number","label":"Advances","value":1},"career":{"value":"","type":"String","label":"Career"},"tests":{"type":"String","label":"Tests","value":"Ranged (Point Blank) with pistols"}},"flags":{},"img":"modules/nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e/icons/talents/quick-draw.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"tDCneZPhhmW4i9bF","name":"Killing Strikes","permission":{"default":0,"lNumE4kwYfzQkIkY":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"type":"String","label":"Description","value":"<p>With expert precision, you can land blows which defy your opponent&rsquo;s ability to counter, chewing through their defenses as surely as an Ogre chews through troll meat. At the start of an encounter, you may spend one Fortune Point to choose to make all your melee attacks for that Round count as having the <em>Fast </em>Quality. This effect lasts for a number of Rounds equal to your level of Killing Strike, though they apply to all of your attacks (i.e. such as extra attacks gained with Talents such as @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.talents.URwIDtInCsxOoGqM]{Dual Wielder}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.talents.hXcfygzujgyMN1uI]{Frenzy} or @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.talents.BlHVzfs0Ow6IYEDw]{Furious Assault}).</p>"},"gmdescription":{"type":"String","label":"Description","value":""},"max":{"type":"String","label":"Max Advances","value":"ws"},"advances":{"type":"Number","label":"Advances","value":1},"career":{"value":"","type":"String","label":"Career"},"tests":{"type":"String","label":"Tests","value":""}},"flags":{},"img":"modules/nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e/icons/talents/killing-strikes.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"v2x3DYSwdj2sK9Bf","name":"Thunderous Charge","permission":{"default":0,"lNumE4kwYfzQkIkY":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"type":"String","label":"Description","value":"<p>The character charges into combat using their body as an additional weapon to push foes away or to the ground. Driven by your rage and momentum, the impact of such a charge can knock a foe flying or bring them to their knees. When the character makes a Charge Action, instead of causing Damage, a successful attack can slam an opponent back 1 yard per SL by which you win the Opposed Test. If this brings them into contact with a wall or other large obstacle, they take Damage equal to the distance travelled in yards, reduced by Toughness Bonus and armor. If they collide with another creature, they take the same Damage as the initial target of the Charge. Once the target is hit, they must then make a <strong>Challenging (+0) Endurance Test</strong> or gain a @Condition[Fatigued] Condition, as the wind is knocked out of them. If they hit a wall or similar obstacle from the charge, the target must make a<strong> Hard (-20) Endurance</strong> Test instead.</p>"},"gmdescription":{"type":"String","label":"Description","value":""},"max":{"type":"String","label":"Max Advances","value":"s"},"advances":{"type":"Number","label":"Advances","value":1},"career":{"value":"","type":"String","label":"Career"},"tests":{"type":"String","label":"Tests","value":"Melee on a Round when you Charge"}},"flags":{},"img":"modules/nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e/icons/talents/thunderous-charge.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"xDEf1fhzhs4tyBGI","name":"Crazed Cook","permission":{"default":0,"lNumE4kwYfzQkIkY":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"type":"String","label":"Description","value":"<p>Once per game session, you may make a <strong>Challenging (+0)@Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.epSHxgJWtT1S0yMY]{Trade (Cook)} Test</strong>. This Action requires at least several minutes. At the GM&rsquo;s discretion, you might gain a bonus to this Test for acquiring certain ingredients to truly enhance your meal. If you succeed, you and your allies gain a <strong>+10 bonus to Willpower Tests</strong> to resist the effects of @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.psychologies.Ib2YQYChktDFN93y]{Fear}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.I0yPc4PH5erWJLmu]{Intimidate} and @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.psychologies.meMkLEwdJIDLxM0B]{Terror} for SL hours or until the end of the session. If the cooking Test succeeds by 6 SL or more, the first time each ally uses a Fortune Point before the end of the effect, that character rolls 1d10. On a result of 6+, that character still gains the benefit of using the Fortune Point, but the Fortune Point does not count as having been expended.</p>"},"gmdescription":{"type":"String","label":"Description","value":""},"max":{"type":"String","label":"Max Advances","value":"dex"},"advances":{"type":"Number","label":"Advances","value":1},"career":{"value":"","type":"String","label":"Career"},"tests":{"type":"String","label":"Tests","value":"Trade (Cook)"}},"flags":{},"img":"modules/nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e/icons/talents/crazed-cook.png","effects":[]}
